A look at the US Air Force's efforts to build an AI-based air combat system, including drones for as little as $3M apiece that serve pilots as a “loyal wingman”

A look at the ethical and legal issues around generative AI, which makes things that were previously only possible on a small scale practical at a massive scale

Tesla faces its first two trials involving fatalities where Autopilot allegedly malfunctioned, in California and Florida state courts in September and October
